Class SaxTagExpanderFilter

java.lang.Object

      ca.hullabaloo.util.sax.SaxTagExpanderFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, org.xml.sax.DTDHandler, org.xml.sax.EntityResolver, org.xml.sax.ErrorHandler, org.xml.sax.XMLFilter, org.xml.sax.XMLReader
public class SaxTagExpanderFilter
extends org.xml.sax.helpers.XMLFilterImpl

Converts escaped tags-escaped-in-text into real elements. This is a pretty limited implementation right now, for example empty tags are not supported. Use with care.

This class is reusable, but not thread safe.

NOTE: This only works across a single ContentHandler.characters(char[], int, int) call, so it should be prefaced with a SaxCharacterConsolidationFilter.

public void setTagWithAttributes(java.lang.String tagName)
Sets the tag we are expanding. This is for tags which may have attributes. Properly-formattted attributes (name and value with double-quoted values) are copied to the new element, others are silently dropped.
